data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. Welcome to Paradise! This is a unique opportunity to make this waterfront home yours.  Home was damaged thanks to Hurricane Ian, has been stripped down to the studs, and is being sold As Is.  So, you can redesign and update this home based on your personal preferences and life style. Located in the “Old Florida” community of Tarpon Ranch Estates, this plantation-style, 3.6-acre retreat on the Myakka River is truly unique with world-class tarpon fishing, equestrian boarding, and 6,500 acres of horseback trails. The gated property boasts 200 feet of direct water frontage on the Myakka River with breathtaking, panoramic views. This a boating and fishing enthusiast's dream.  You are only minutes to Charlotte Harbor and then on to the Gulf of Mexico. The current floor plan features 5 bedrooms, 3 baths and a private studio apartment. When you enter the home, you are immediately entering the grand 14-foot foyer with staircase leading up to the living and dining areas with windows and sliders leading to the deck providing expansive water views. Balconies, sun decks, and numerous windows throughout provide spectacular view from almost every room, and the master suite opens to a private balcony providing an exceptional water view. The ground floor consists of a 3.5 car carport, ample storage area, and several other rooms that could be your gym, home theater, or craft room, and there's room for a pickle ball court! Plus, new roof was installed in 2018. So if you are ready to put your personal touches to this exceptional home, make your appointment today.
